  "topic_name": "Measurement of Length, Mass and Capacity",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Measurement helps us find how long, heavy, or much space something takes. We use standard units like millimetre (mm), centimetre (cm), metre (m), and kilometre (km) for length; gram (g) and kilogram (kg) for mass; and millilitre (ml) and litre (l) for capacity. We can add and subtract these measurements to solve problems.",
    "rules": [
      "For length: 1 km = 1000 m, 1 m = 100 cm, 1 cm = 10 mm",
      "For mass: 1 kg = 1000 g",
      "For capacity: 1 l = 1000 ml",
      "When adding or subtracting, convert to the same unit first",
      "Always write the unit with your answer"
    ]
  },
